You will need the following:

-Access to Zoom

-Download R (base) 
R is a programming language that is especially powerful for data exploration, visualization, and statistical analysis. To interact with R, we use RStudio.
Go here https://cran.r-project.org/mirrors.html
for LV -> Choose USA > University of Utah link and follow download instructions


-Download R Studio
go here https://posit.co/download/rstudio-desktop/
** If on Mac scroll down on the page to get access to Mac download

Once all downloads are complete, open R studio and check to make sure a white window with some panes pops up 


You are now ready for R Basics

